  +edit('https://github.com/logux/logux.io/blob/main/src/branding.pug')
    +title1
      |  Branding Guidelines

  p.text_block Logux visual identity is based on #[a( href="https://twitter.com/andreysitnik/status/1258058327029841928" ) #[strong Linguopunk] philosophy]: language and writing system diversity, combining digital culture with old writing systems. You can find inspiration in #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk" ) Twitter account].

  p.text_block
    | Few examples: #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/925633915401973761" ) English in Korean style], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/834375284187095040" ) Modern Gothic Calligraphy], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/897729669289693186" ) Round-robin], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/849169543520038912" ) Kufic script], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/973831384585375744" ) English as Japanese stamps], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/1008982998140837888" ) Persian calligraphy], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/852068906680373248" ) Arabic calligraphy], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/814456903099158528" ) Andrey Martynov], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/924033568543821824" ) Georgian calligraphy], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/813716142275567616" ) Valentine Sidorov], #[a( href="https://twitter.com/linguopunk/status/1011519731826937856" ) old books].

  h2 Logo with Name
